**REDSHIFT Database**

This database in general was created to mainly store the **RAW** data of transactions (purchases) made to different people who have accounts in our allied banks. In addition, we also have materialized views[\*](#materialized-view) in this database, which show us the analysis of the sales behavior of the stores according to their **COMMERCIAL DISTRICT** as well as the customers who made purchases in them

# **Ncr\_transactions**

***Objective:** This table aims to save all the transactions that are sent by NCR, these transactions are in “raw” form.*

* The **NAME OF THE FILE** from which we took The information  
* The **FIID** of which The user is part ( credit card)  
* The **ID of The ACCOUNT** in your FIID  
* **The DATE** on which The transaction was made (*posted\_at*),   
* **The DESCRIPTORS** (*with which we can decipher which entity the user purchased*)

![][image1]

  * Descriptors  
* [MAIN Schema](https://docs.google.com/document/d/10Sq0jrrBCUobCR7zpleAEeFBvxtFXG7Gb-QWop4_wXo/edit)

# **Processed\_transactions**

***Objective:** This table is made to store the transaction information from the Ncr\_trasanctions table after it has been processed and resolved. In this table there is a field called **brand\_name\_ml** in which we can know if the transaction was resolved by BRAND\_ML\_API*

*T*his table has (among others) some fields that are worth highlighting:

* The **NAME OF THE FILE** from which we took The information  
* The **FIID** of which The user is part ( credit card)  
* The **ID of The ACCOUNT** in your FIID  
* **The DATE** on which The transaction was made (*posted\_at*),   
* **The DESCRIPTORS** (*with which we can decipher which entity the user purchased*)  
* The **Value of the transaction**   
* **Type of currency used**   
* The **BRAND\_ID** (*which is the ID of The Brands table of The TX\_DB schema*)  
* **TRX\_TYPE** of the transaction (*to know if the transaction is in one of the purchase categories that we are interested in studying*)  
* **The DATE** on which The transaction was made (*posted\_at*)  
* **BRAND\_NAME\_ML** este campo guarda el nombre de las marcas que fueron resueltas por **ml\_brand\_api**

# **Appendix**

## **Materialized View** {#materialized-view}

A materialized view is a database object that stores the precomputed results of a query, essentially acting like a cached copy of data from one or more base tables, allowing for faster retrieval of that data compared to running the query against the base tables directly; it's essentially a physical table containing the results of a complex query, improving performance for frequently executed queries that access the same data subset.
